court ruling on the census. The decision outlawing sampling means
that the Clinton administration faces the prospect of vetoing a
spending bill this fall and, perhaps shutting down the Commerce,
Justice and State departments to defend a method for taking the
census that the courts say is illegal. By Steven A. Holmes.
