<P>
   WINDOWS-SOMMELIER (New York) _ When Andrea Immer bounds up to a
table at Windows on the World, she faces diners who invariably seem
wary. Dressed in her severe black pantsuit and white blouse, she is
clearly not the waitress. She did not welcome them at the door so
she is neither hostess nor maitre d'. And her greeting is so
relentlessly energetic, there is a fleeting suspicion she might try
recruiting volunteers for the hokey pokey. What almost no one
assumes _ with her brisk demeanor that seems part corporate
executive, part kindergarten teacher _ is that she is the
sommelier, overseeing a cellar that accounts for $5 million in wine
sales per year. Not only that, but she is was judged the best
sommelier in the country last year by the Sommelier Society of
America. By Alex Witchel.
