A1377 &Cx1f; ttx-z
r l &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-TRIVIA-Q&AMP;A-TEX     08-25 0364
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-TRIVIA-Q&AMP;A-TEX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
A FRACTION OF MONTSERRAT RESIDENTS STILL LIVE THERE
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By ROGERS CADENHEAD 
c.1998 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   Q: I haven't heard much about Montserrat since last year's
evacuations. What's the status today?
</P>
<P>
   _ D.T.H., Burleson, Texas
</P>
<P>
   A: About 3,000 people remain on the northern third of the
Caribbean island, the only region that can be inhabited due to its
distance from the active Soufriere Hills volcano.
</P>
<P>
   The largest eruption in six months occurred in July, sending ash
and debris across the 39-square-mile island.
</P>
<P>
   The British territory had 11,000 residents in July 1995 when the
volcano became active after four centuries of dormancy, killing 20
people and destroying the capital city of Plymouth.
</P>
<P>
   Montserrat refugees were recently given permission to
permanently settle in the United Kingdom.
</P>
<P>
   Q: Are Strat-O-Matic games still being produced? My grandson's a
baseball nut, and I'd like to surprise him with one.
</P>
<P>
   _ C.A., New Philadelphia, Ohio
</P>
<P>
   A: This year, Strat-O-Matic is celebrating the 40th anniversary
of the first game designed by founder Harold Richman.
</P>
<P>
   Today, the Glen Head, N.Y., company produces baseball, football,
basketball and hockey games. There also are software versions of
its baseball and basketball games.
</P>
<P>
   For ordering information, call (800) 645-3455 or write to
Strat-O-Matic Game Co., 46 Railroad Plaza, Glen Head, NY 11545.
</P>
<P>
   Q: I remember reading that Monty Hall's daughter is an actress.
Who is she?
</P>
<P>
   _ J.G., Arlington
</P>
<P>
   A: Hall and Marilyn Plottel are the parents of Joanna Gleason,
48.
</P>
<P>
   Gleason, a Tony and Theatre award-winner for her stage work, was
a regular on the TV series ``Love &AMP; War'' and ``Temporarily
Yours.''
</P>
<P>
   She has appeared in the films ``Boogie Nights,'' ``Mr. Holland's
Opus,'' ``Crimes and Misdemeanors'' and ``Hannah and Her Sisters.''
</P>
<P>
   (Rogers Cadenhead writes a trivia column for the Fort Worth
Star-Telegram. He can be reached at the Star-Telegram, Box 1870,
Fort Worth, Texas 76101; or by E-mail at trivia(at)prefect.com.
Visit the Star-Telegram's online services on the World Wide Web:
www.star-telegram.com) &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
