<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-HOW-TO-EAT-A-NAPOLEAN-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
EATING A NAPOLEAN: NEVER AGAIN NEED IT GO SQUISH OR FALL TO
PIECES 
</HEADLINE>
   c.1998 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   The napoleon, however beautiful, poses a serious challenge to
the diner: how to attack? There is a trick to getting a taste of
each layer without squishing the whole. Resist the temptation to
use the side of the fork. Instead, plunge the fork boldly in near a
corner, tines down, with a single stroke. It should go all the way
through without crushing the layers. Repeat at a sharp angle to the
first stroke, then pull away the bite. The remaining napoleon
should remain unscathed.
</P>
</TEXT>
