<SLUG> BC-BONNIE-WTHRCHAN-FACTS-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;    
 &HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Eyeing the facts and figures
 &HT;    By Phil Kloer
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   The Weather Channel
</P>
<P>
   Based: Marietta, Georgia.
</P>
<P>
   Reach: Available in about 72 million U.S. homes, plus 2 million
more in Latin America and some exposure in Europe. The Weather
Channel also provides weather to 250 radio stations and weather
page maps and forecasts to newspapers. Its Web page,
http://www.weather.com, gets about 90 million hits per month.
</P>
<P>
   Started: 1982.
</P>
<P>
   Ratings: Generally low, but increase dramatically during
hurricanes. During Hurricane Fran in 1996, ratings topped out at
more than 2 million viewers at one point.
</P>
<P>
   Owner: Landmark Communications Inc. in Norfolk, Va., a privately
owned media company that includes about 200 (mostly small)
newspapers, a 50 percent stake in Auto Trader magazines and
InfniNet, an Internet access service.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
