<SLUG> BC-MEDICAL-BOUTIQUE-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;    
 &HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Hospital boutique caters to the needs of women
 &HT;    By Marylin Johnson
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   ATLANTA _A woman's place is no longer just in the home. It can
also be at Northside Hospital's new boutique called ``A Woman's
Place.''
</P>
<P>
   The boutique, which has its grand opening on Thursday,
specializes in clothing and products relating to oncology,
maternity and incontinence. The 1,000-square-foot shop is decorated
in gold and burgundy and will stock motivational, educational and
inspirational books and tapes.
</P>
<P>
   In addition to health-care products, the boutique will have
personnel on hand to answer questions about products, help with
fittings and to listen to health-care concerns.
</P>
<P>
   ``It's women caring for women,'' says manager Beth Allen, who
spearheaded the two-year effort to open the boutique. Allen, an
obstetrics nurse, helped develop the Perinatal and Lactation Center
in Northside Hospital after discovering that many women needed help
with breast-feeding techniques.
</P>
<P>
   But Allen had bigger ideas. She wanted a place to house products
and services in one convenient location for women in their
childbearing years through menopause and beyond. Allen says her
goal was to create a warm environment where women could feel
comfortable and safe.
</P>
<P>
   ``We want women to feel pretty while going through treatments,''
she says. ``That's why we have a line of jewelry as well as scarves
and hats.''
</P>
<P>
   Much of the clothing and products will be covered by a woman's
insurance carrier. Prices are comparable to those in retail stores.
For example, nursing bras range from $25 to $35; wigs $130-$220;
reusable incontinent undergarments $12-$15; jewelry $8-$30;
compression hosiery $12-$80.
</P>
<P>
   Next May, ``A Woman's Place'' will move to the new five-story
Northside Hospital's Women's Center on Hollis Cobb Drive in
Atlanta. Another boutique is planned for late 1999 in Alpharetta,
in the Northside/Alpharetta Medical Office Building which will
offer out-patient services.
</P>
<P>
   ``A Woman's Place'' will be open 9 a.m. -5 p.m. Mondays-Fridays;
by appointment Saturdays. 980 Johnson Ferry Road, Atlanta.
404-845-5125.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
