   KILLER BULLS &QL;
</P>
<P>
   FORT WORTH, Texas _ Cody Hart drew a notorious bull named Red
Wolf at a rodeo last year in Alexandria, La. Some 2 1/2 years
before, Red Wolf had fatally stomped Brent Thurman at the 1994
National Finals Rodeo. Hart, a nationally ranked cowboy who lives
in Thackerville, Okla., stayed on Red Wolf for the mandatory eight
seconds that day and posted a score of 94 out of a possible 100. He
survived an encounter with a growing, flesh-and-blood reality of
the sport: Crowd-pleasing bulls with feisty reputations have become
the marquee attractions on today's multimillion-dollar pro rodeo
circuit. By BRETT HOFFMAN. Story has moved in ``a'' general news
category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
