   SWINDELL-BOOKSHELF &QL;
</P>
<P>
   UNDATED _ In selecting both judiciously and capriciously those
works that would be anointed as the 100 best novels published in
English in the 20th century, the editorial board members of the
Modern Library made certain that Henry James would be aboard. No
matter that Henry Junior of the elegant James clan is a
19th-century figure whose greatest works all appeared in print
before the century's turn. But a protest may be in order because
other notable 19th-century folk who wrote into the 20th century
were rudely ignored. By LARRY SWINDELL. Story has moved in ``l''
lifestyle category. &QL; 
