<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-FBC-CSUN-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
CSUN OFFENSE GETS BOOST FROM TRANSFER
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By HOWARD BECK  
 c.1998 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ Cal State Northridge's offensive line got a boost
Tuesday when Mike Barnes, a reserve guard at Arizona State, was
cleared by the NCAA to transfer to CSUN and play for the Matadors.
</P>
<P>
   Barnes, a 6-foot-2, 276-pound senior, hasn't played for ASU
since the Sun Bowl last Dec. 31 and quit in the offseason, a school
spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
   A product of Norco High in Riverside County, Barnes played
sparingly at ASU, starting two games in 1997, one in 1996 and four
in 1995, each time filling in for an injured starter. But CSUN head
coach Ron Ponciano figures Barnes will make an immediate impact at
the Division I-AA level. Barnes will join the Matadors in training
camp within a few days.
</P>
<P>
   ``He'll be a huge benefit to us,'' Ponciano said. ``He's either
going to start or give us incredible depth. You would think he
could start here at Northridge if he can start at Arizona State.''
</P>
<P>
   In any case, Barnes will add experience to a line that, right
now, would be composed entirely of freshmen on the right side _ Tim
Shoffeit at guard and Keith Kincade at tackle.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
